<p>
	Wooden incense smoke box with intricate fretwork design for incense stick and cone burning and storage. The box is made from a natural fair trade Sheesham hardwood, and is beautifully finished with a soft wax sheen. It has been cut with the fretwork pattern along the lid. Each end of the box has small drilled holes inside in which incense sticks can be placed for burning and on the base there is two brass wells for burning incense cones. The lid can then be closed as the incense is burning allowing the smoke and aroma escapes through the fretwork. The hinges are brass there is also a hidden compartment under the box in which incense sticks can be stored with a secret door on the end. Dimensions: Length 30cms. Designs may vary slightly.</p>
